## 1. Core Philosophy & Architecture Overview

*Question: How do we decouple light simulation from pixel rendering without breaking visual consistency?*

**Answer:** By abandoning the atomic frame model. We divide the frame into three asynchronous layers, each mapped to specific GPU hardware queues. The Compositor assumes that `BACKGROUND` data is inherently "stale" and uses `DYNAMIC` reprojection to align it with `LIVE` geometry.

### Hardware Queue Mapping
| Layer | Hardware Unit | Refresh Target | V-Sync Linked? |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **LIVE** | Graphics Queue (SMs) | 16.6ms (60fps+) | YES |
| **DYNAMIC** | Async Compute / Tensor Cores | 16.6ms (60fps+) | YES |
| **BACKGROUND**| Async Compute Queue | 33ms - 66ms (Staggered) | NO |

