## 4. The Compositing Shader (GLSL Implementation)

*Question: What is the exact math to glue a "stale" background onto a "live" moving frame?*

**Answer:** We sample the motion vector of the current pixel, apply it to the UV coordinates of the previous frame, and sample the stale GI texture. We then use a depth-check to ensure we aren't reprojecting background data onto a newly exposed foreground object.

### Compositor GLSL Pseudo-Code

```glsl
#version 450
// Inputs
layout(binding = 0) uniform sampler2D tex_live_color;
layout(binding = 1) uniform sampler2D tex_live_depth;
layout(binding = 2) uniform sampler2D tex_motion_vectors;
layout(binding = 3) uniform sampler3D tex_stale_gi_volume; // From BACKGROUND

// Outputs
layout(location = 0) out vec4 FinalPixel;

void main() {
    vec2 uv = In.UV;
    
    // 1. Get Live Data
    vec4 live_albedo = texture(tex_live_color, uv);
    float live_depth = texture(tex_live_depth, uv);
    vec2 motion = texture(tex_motion_vectors, uv).xy;
    
    // 2. Reproject History (DYNAMIC Tier Math)
    vec2 history_uv = uv - motion;
    
    // 3. Disocclusion Check (Are we looking at something new?)
    float history_depth = GetHistoryDepth(history_uv);
    float depth_delta = abs(live_depth - history_depth);
    
    vec4 gi_contribution;
    if (depth_delta > DEPTH_TOLERANCE) {
        // DISOCCLUSION DETECTED: Fallback to low-quality ambient or screen-space
        gi_contribution = FallbackAmbient(); 
    } else {
        // VALID HISTORY: Sample the 3D Voxel Grid using World Position
        vec3 world_pos = ReconstructWorldPos(uv, live_depth);
        gi_contribution = texture(tex_stale_gi_volume, world_pos * grid_scale);
        
        // Tensor Denoise Weighting would be applied here
    }
    
    // 4. Final Layer Composition
    FinalPixel = live_albedo * gi_contribution;
}

```

